utility designed to optimize academic time management. As a student in the Mosul region aiming for global excellence, I developed this tool to address a common challenge: inefficient study time allocation. The program utilizes a weighted algorithm to distribute available study hours across multiple subjects based on their individual difficulty levels, ensuring that more demanding topics receive the focus they require.
​Key Features:
​Dynamic Time Allocation: Dynamically calculates study duration per subject using a weighted distribution logic.
​User-Centric Design: Simple, interactive CLI (Command Line Interface) for quick scheduling.
​Scalability: The algorithm can be easily adapted to include priority tags or subject-specific deadlines in future versions.
​Why I Built This:
I believe that technology should be an enabler for academic success. This project represents my commitment to combining logical programming with practical daily problem-solving. By automating the planning process, I can dedicate more of my cognitive resources to deep learning and mastery of the curriculum.
​Technical Stack:
​Language: Python 3.x
​Logic: Algorithmic Weighted Distribution
